x4freetext: CV-28
Natural metal Ti, Ni and Cu foils from Goodfellow,
England, more details can be found in
J,ARI,44,687,93 For Ti
J,ARI,42,513,91 For Ni
Stacks were irradiated in vacuum.
Beam current was monitored by Faraday-cup.
The incident beam energy was controlled by magnetic
deflection at Rez and Debrecen cyclotron and
was normalized to other monitor reaction at Juelich
cyclotron.
Normal high resolution gamma-spectrometry was
applied.
The beam energy degradation in the targets was
calculated according to Williamson et al., Report
Correction was made for dead time, pile-up and cascade
losses.
counting statistics
detector S efficiency 5%,
decay data 3%,
number of target nuclei 1%,
incident bombarding particle
intensity 7-9%.
The total estimated errors in the cross
sections are 6-15%
Changed to lower case, BIB updates
SD: Small correction of REACTION code was
made in Subents 002-007. SF9 was deleted as obsolete.
ERR-ANALYS was added to Subent 001.
Numerical data were received from the authors
The total errors in the cross sections were
obtained by summing quadratically the possible
individual relative errors, described in Subent 001.
the uncertainty varying in accordance with
the straggling, the foil non-uniformities and
the calculation method
